Class FinalKillEvent

java.lang.Object
org.bukkit.event.Event
com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.game.GameEvent
com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.game.FinalKillEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cancellable
public class FinalKillEvent extends GameEvent implements Cancellable
Use this event to process code every time a player is final killed
This could be used to add particle effects or custom functionality (like adding to stats) to final kills
Author:
YeetManLord
See Also:
  • BedwarsPlayer.onDeath to view what exactly happens when a player is final killed
API Note:
If you are going to cancel the event you must handle what happens to the revived player If you just want the player to die normally use setNonFinal(boolean) instead of canceling
